    dc:date "2008" ;
    dc:title "On a new genus of endemic millipedes (Diplopoda: Chordeumatida: Anthroleucosomatidae) from the Balkan Peninsula" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.181580> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.181580>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14 – 16. General scheme of anterior and posterior gonopods in different anthroleucosomatidan genera. 14 — anterior gonopods, oral view: a—sternal process (as in the genus Ghilarovia Guliċka, 1972); b—anterior central elements (as in the genus Alloiopus Attems, 1951); c—anterior sternal sac (as in the genus Adshardicus Golovatch, 1981); d—telopodite (as in the genus Anamastigona Silvestri, 1898); e—lateral parts [as in the genera Alloiopus (right half) and Dacosoma Tabacaru, 1967 (left half)]. 15 — anterior gonopods, caudal view: f—posterior acute lamella (as in the genus Ghilarovia); g—claw-like branch (as in the genus Camptogona Brölemann, 1935); h—syncoxite (as in the genus Serbosoma Ć urċiċ & Makarov, 2000); i—unpaired central process (as in the genus Bulgarosoma Verhoeff, 1926); j—lateral part (as in the genus Bulgarosoma). 16 — posterior gonopods: k—anterior triangular lamella (as in the genus Ghilarovia); l—sternal process (as in the genus Dacosoma); m—telopodites (as in the genus Anthroleucosoma Verhoeff, 1899); ncoxal processes (as in the genus Alloiopus); p—angiocoxites (as in the genus Anamastigona); r—colpocoxites (as in the genus Anamastigona); t—coxites (as in the genus Caucaseuma Strasser, 1970)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/181580/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

